50|$|Anthoxanthum aristatum is {{a species}} of grass known by the common names awned vernalgrass or <b>annual</b> <b>vernalgrass.</b> It is native to North Africa and {{southern}} and western Europe {{as far north as}} the Netherlands, and it is known in other regions, including northern Europe and North America, as an introduced species. It is occasionally a minor weed of fields. This is an annual grass growing in small tufts up to about 30 centimeters tall. The leaves are short, pointed, and somewhat hairy. The inflorescence is up to 3 centimeters long and one wide, flat and hairy with spikelets a few millimeters long.|$|E

